        "text": " this reservation upon the preceding general statement. The author of Kings, having said nothing of Uzziah’s sacrilege, had no need to make such an exception.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the people did yet corruptly.—Still used to deal corruptly; a paraphrase of what we read in 2Kings 15:35, “the people still used to sacrifice and burn incense on the high places.” We know further, from the extant utterances of the prophets of those days, that a deep-seated moral corruption was sapping the strength of the nation. (Comp. Micah 3:10-12; Hosea 4:1-2.)",
