  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 2.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Howbeit",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This word purports to render the Hebrew ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "רַק",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which might find a more telling reproduction in such a phrase as \"and moreover.\" It has been said, wherein his father did right, so did he; and to his clear advantage, where his father went wrong, he did riot. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The people did yet corruptly",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The parallel, in its ver. 35, specifies in what this ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "consisted, viz.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that they continued the high places, burning incense and sacrificing at them. The early chapters of Isaiah depict forcibly the extent of this national apostasy, and the heinous offensiveness of it in the Divine sight. 2 Chronicles 27:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Jotham having ascended the throne at the age of twenty-five, reigned altogether in the spirit and power of his father, with the single limitation that he did not go into the sanctuary of Jahve (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 26:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".). This remark is not found in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", because there Uzziah's intrusion into the temple is also omitted. The people still did corruptly (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 26:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This refers, indeed, to the continuation of the worship in the high places, but hints also at the deep moral corruption which the prophets of that time censure (cf. especially ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 2:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 5:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 1:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
